e_star.svg/32px-Featured_article_star.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="180" data-file-height="180" /></a></span>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Scientology" title="Portal:Scientology">Scientology</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Shinto" title="Portal:Shinto">Shinto</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Theosophy" title="Portal:Theosophy">Theosophy</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Wicca" title="Portal:Wicca">Wicca</a>&#160;</li>\n<li>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Portal:Zoroastrianism" title="Portal:Zoroastrianism">Zoroastrianism</a>&#160;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<table width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="10" style="background:#000066; border-style:solid; border-width:5px; border-color:#000066; border-bottom:0px">\n<tr>\n<td style="vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;">\n<p><span style="float:center; width:100%; font:normal small-caps 50px/50px sans-serif; font-family:Century Gothic; color:Gold"><b>Vajrayana Buddhism Portal</b></span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<table width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="10" style="background:#000066; border-style:solid; border-width:5px; border-color:#000066; border-top:0px">\n<tr>\n<td style="vertical-align:top;">\n<div style="clear:both; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #B00760; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #B00760; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="What_is_Vajrayana.3F">What is Vajrayana?</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #B00760; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #E0C0D0;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:102px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Digug.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Digug.jpg/100px-Digug.jpg" width="100" height="150" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Digug.jpg/150px-Digug.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/66/Digug.jpg/200px-Digug.jpg 2x" data-file-width="333" data-file-height="500" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Digug.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nA <i>digug</i> <i><a href="/wiki/Dorje" class="mw-redirect" title="Dorje">dorje</a></i>.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>Vajray\xc4\x81na</b> (<a href="/wiki/Sanskrit_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Sanskrit language">Sanskrit</a>: \xe0\xa4\xb5\xe0\xa4\x9c\xe0\xa5\x8d\xe0\xa4\xb0\xe0\xa4\xaf\xe0\xa4\xbe\xe0\xa4\xa8; <a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: \xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\x9c\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xa8; <a href="/wiki/Devanagari" title="Devanagari">Devanagari</a>: \xe0\xa4\xb5\xe0\xa4\x9c\xe0\xa5\x8d\xe0\xa4\xb0\xe0\xa4\xaf\xe0\xa4\xbe\xe0\xa4\xa8; <a href="/wiki/Sinhala_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Sinhala language">Sinhala</a>: \xe0\xb7\x80\xe0\xb6\xa2\xe0\xb7\x8a\xe2\x80\x8d\xe0\xb6\xbb\xe0\xb6\xba\xe0\xb7\x8f\xe0\xb6\xb1; <a href="/wiki/Malayalam" title="Malayalam">Malayalam</a>: \xe0\xb4\xb5\xe0\xb4\x9c\xe0\xb5\x8d\xe0\xb4\xb0\xe0\xb4\xaf\xe0\xb4\xbe\xe0\xb4\xa8; <a href="/wiki/Oriya_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Oriya language">Oriya</a>: \xe0\xac\xac\xe0\xac\x9c\xe0\xad\x8d\xe0\xac\xb0\xe0\xac\xaf\xe0\xac\xbe\xe0\xac\xa8; <a href="/wiki/Standard_Tibetan" title="Standard Tibetan">Tibetan</a>: \xe0\xbd\xa2\xe0\xbe\xa1\xe0\xbd\xbc\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\xa2\xe0\xbe\x97\xe0\xbd\xba\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\x90\xe0\xbd\xba\xe0\xbd\x82\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\x94\xe0\xbc\x8b, rdo rje theg pa; <a href="/wiki/Mongolian_language" title="Mongolian language">Mongolian</a>: \xd0\x9e\xd1\x87\xd0\xb8\xd1\x80\xd1\x82 \xd1\x85\xd3\xa9\xd0\xbb\xd0\xb3\xd3\xa9\xd0\xbd, <i>Ochirt H\xc3\xb6lg\xc3\xb6n</i>; <a href="/wiki/Chinese_language" title="Chinese language">Chinese</a>: \xe9\x87\x91\xe5\x89\x9b\xe4\xb9\x98, pinyin: J\xc4\xabng\xc4\x81ng ch\xc3\xa9ng), also known as <b>Tantric Buddhism</b>, <b>Tantray\xc4\x81na</b>, <b>Mantray\xc4\x81na</b>, <b>Secret Mantra</b>, <b>Esoteric Buddhism</b> and the <b>Diamond Way</b> or <b>Thunderbolt Way</b>, is a complex and multifaceted system of <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhist</a> thought and practice which evolved over several centuries.</p>\n<p>According to Vajray\xc4\x81na scriptures "Vajray\xc4\x81na" refers to one of three vehicles or <a href="/wiki/Yana_(Buddhism)" title="Yana (Buddhism)">routes to enlightenment</a>, the other two being the <a href="/wiki/Hinayana" title="Hinayana">Hinay\xc4\x81na</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mahayana" title="Mahayana">Mahayana</a>. Note that Hinay\xc4\x81na (or <a href="/wiki/Nikaya_Buddhism" title="Nikaya Buddhism">Nikaya</a>) is not to be confused with <a href="/wiki/Theravada" title="Theravada">Theravada</a> (a practice lineage); although is sometimes equated to it. Founded by the <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">Indian</a> <a href="/wiki/Mah%C4%81siddha" class="mw-redirect" title="Mah\xc4\x81siddha">Mah\xc4\x81siddhas</a>, Vajray\xc4\x81na subscribes to Buddhist <a href="/wiki/Tantric" class="mw-disambig" title="Tantric">tantric</a> literature.</p>\n<p>Although the first tantric Buddhist texts appeared in India in the 3rd century and continued to appear until the 12th century, scholars such as Hirakawa Akira assert that the Vajray\xc4\x81na probably came into existence in the 6th or 7th century, while the term Vajray\xc4\x81na itself first appeared in the 8th century.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Vajrayana" title="Vajrayana">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center; margin:0.25em auto 0.75em"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><b>Show new selections</b></span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #B00760; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #B00760; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_article/5&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article">Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #B00760; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #E0C0D0;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="thumb tnone">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:152px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Vajradhara7.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Vajradhara7.jpg/150px-Vajradhara7.jpg" width="150" height="203" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Vajradhara7.jpg/225px-Vajradhara7.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Vajradhara7.jpg/300px-Vajradhara7.jpg 2x" data-file-width="720" data-file-height="972" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Vajradhara7.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n<a href="/wiki/Vajradhara" title="Vajradhara">Vajradhara</a>, the tantric form of <a href="/wiki/Shakyamuni" class="mw-redirect" title="Shakyamuni">Shakyamuni</a>, teacher of the <a href="/wiki/Tantra" title="Tantra">tantra</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>Mahasiddha</b> (<a href="/wiki/Tibetan_alphabet" title="Tibetan alphabet">Tibetan</a>: <span lang="bo" style="font-family: \'Qomolangma-Dunhuang\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sarchen\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sarchung\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Suring\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sutung\', \'Qomolangma-Title\', \'Qomolangma-Subtitle\', \'Qomolangma-Woodblock\', \'DDC Uchen\', \'DDC Rinzin\', Kailash, Jomolhari, \'TCRC Youtso Unicode\', \'Tibetan Machine Uni\', Wangdi29, \'Noto Sans Tibetan\', \'Microsoft Himalaya\'; font-size:1.25em; vertical-align:top; word-wrap: break-word;" xml:lang="bo">\xe0\xbd\x82\xe0\xbe\xb2\xe0\xbd\xb4\xe0\xbd\x96\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\x90\xe0\xbd\xbc\xe0\xbd\x96\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\x86\xe0\xbd\xba\xe0\xbd\x93\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\x94\xe0\xbd\xbc</span>,&#160;<a href="/wiki/Wylie_transliteration" title="Wylie transliteration">Wylie</a>: <i>grub thob chen po</i>; or <a href="/wiki/Tibetan_alphabet" title="Tibetan alphabet">Tibetan</a>: <span lang="bo" style="font-family: \'Qomolangma-Dunhuang\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sarchen\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sarchung\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Suring\', \'Qomolangma-Uchen Sutung\', \'Qomolangma-Title\', \'Qomolangma-Subtitle\', \'Qomolangma-Woodblock\', \'DDC Uchen\', \'DDC Rinzin\', Kailash, Jomolhari, \'TCRC Youtso Unicode\', \'Tibetan Machine Uni\', Wangdi29, \'Noto Sans Tibetan\', \'Microsoft Himalaya\'; font-size:1.25em; vertical-align:top; word-wrap: break-word;" xml:lang="bo">\xe0\xbd\x8f\xe0\xbd\xb4\xe0\xbd\xa3\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\xa4\xe0\xbd\xb4\xe0\xbd\x82</span>,&#160;<a href="/wiki/Wylie_transliteration" title="Wylie transliteration">Wylie</a>: <i>tul shug</i>; Sanskrit Devanagari: \xe0\xa4\xae\xe0\xa4\xb9\xe0\xa4\xbe\xe0\xa4\xb8\xe0\xa4\xbf\xe0\xa4\xa6\xe0\xa5\x8d\xe0\xa4\xa7; <a href="/wiki/IAST" class="mw-redirect" title="IAST">IAST</a>: mah\xc4\x81siddha, <i>maha</i> meaning "great" and <i>siddha</i> meaning "adept") is a term for someone who embodies and cultivates the "<a href="/wiki/Siddhi" title="Siddhi">siddhi</a> of perfection." They are a certain type of <a href="/wiki/Yoga" title="Yoga">yogin/yogini</a> recognized in <a href="/wiki/Vajrayana" title="Vajrayana">Vajrayana</a> Buddhism.</p>\n<p>Mahasiddhas were <a href="/wiki/Tantra" title="Tantra">tantric</a> practitioners, or <i>tantrikas</i> who had sufficient <a href="/wiki/Empowerment_(Vajrayana)" title="Empowerment (Vajrayana)">empowerments</a> and teachings to act as a <a href="/wiki/Guru" title="Guru">guru</a> or tantric master.</p>\n<p>A <i>siddha</i> is an individual who, through the practice of <i><a href="/wiki/Sadhana" class="mw-redirect" title="Sadhana">sadhana</a></i>, attains the realization of <a href="/wiki/Siddhis" class="mw-redirect" title="Siddhis">siddhis</a>, psychic and spiritual abilities and powers. Their historical influence throughout the <a href="/wiki/Indian_subcontinent" title="Indian subcontinent">Indic</a> and <a href="/wiki/Himalayas" title="Himalayas">Himalayan</a> region was vast and they reached mythic proportions which is codified in their <a href="/wiki/Songs_of_realization" title="Songs of realization">songs of realization</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hagiography" title="Hagiography">hagiographies</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Namthar" class="mw-redirect" title="Namthar">namthar</a>, many of which have been preserved in the <a href="/wiki/Tibetan_Buddhist_canon" title="Tibetan Buddhist canon">Tibetan Buddhist canon</a>.</p>\n<p>The Mahasiddhas are the founders of <a href="/wiki/Vajrayana" title="Vajrayana">Vajrayana</a> traditions and <a href="/wiki/Lineage_(Buddhism)" title="Lineage (Buddhism)">lineages</a>, such as <a href="/wiki/Dzogchen" title="Dzogchen">Dzogchen</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mahamudra" title="Mahamudra">Mahamudra</a>.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Nominate/Selected_article&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Nominate/Selected article (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_article&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Selected article (page does not exist)">More articles...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #B00760; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #B00760; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_concept/3&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_concept">Selected concept</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #B00760; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #E0C0D0;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:152px;"><a href="/wiki/File:KalachakraSera.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/KalachakraSera.jpg/150px-KalachakraSera.jpg" width="150" height="150" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/KalachakraSera.jpg/225px-KalachakraSera.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/KalachakraSera.jpg/300px-KalachakraSera.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1302" data-file-height="1305" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:KalachakraSera.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nKalachakra <a href="/wiki/Thangka" title="Thangka">thangka</a> from the <a href="/wiki/Sera_Monastery" title="Sera Monastery">Sera Monastery</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>In <a href="/wiki/Tibetan_Buddhism" title="Tibetan Buddhism">Tibetan Buddhist</a> and Indian Hindu/Buddhist traditions, <b>Shambhala</b> (also spelled <b>Shambala</b> or <b>Shamballa</b>; <a href="/wiki/Standard_Tibetan" title="Standard Tibetan">Tibetan</a>: \xe0\xbd\x96\xe0\xbd\x91\xe0\xbd\xba\xe0\xbc\x8b\xe0\xbd\xa0\xe0\xbd\x96\xe0\xbe\xb1\xe0\xbd\xb4\xe0\xbd\x84\xe0\xbc\x8b; <a href="/wiki/Wylie_transliteration" title="Wylie transliteration">Wylie</a>: <i>bde \'byung</i>, pron. de-jung; <a href="/wiki/Chinese_language" title="Chinese language">Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh" xml:lang="zh">\xe9\xa6\x99\xe5\xb7\xb4\xe6\x8b\x89</span>; <a href="/wiki/Pinyin" title="Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-pinyin" xml:lang="zh-Latn-pinyin">xi\xc4\x81ngb\xc4\x81l\xc4\x81</span></i>) is a <a href="/wiki/Monarchy" title="Monarchy">kingdom</a> hidden somewhere in <a href="/wiki/Inner_Asia" title="Inner Asia">Inner Asia</a>. It is mentioned in various ancient texts, including the <a href="/wiki/Kalachakra" title="Kalachakra">Kalachakra Tantra</a> and the ancient texts of the <a href="/wiki/Zhang_Zhung" class="mw-redirect" title="Zhang Zhung">Zhang Zhung</a> culture which predated Tibetan Buddhism in western <a href="/wiki/Tibet" title="Tibet">Tibet</a>. The <a href="/wiki/B%C3%B6n" class="mw-redirect" title="B\xc3\xb6n">B\xc3\xb6n</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> scriptures speak of a closely related land called <a href="/wiki/Tagzig_Olmo_Lung_Ring" title="Tagzig Olmo Lung Ring">Olmolungring</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Hinduism" title="Hinduism">Hindu</a> texts such as <a href="/wiki/Vishnu_Purana" title="Vishnu Purana">Vishnu Purana</a> mention Shambhala as the birth place of <a href="/wiki/Kalki" title="Kalki">Kalki</a>, the final incarnation of <a href="/wiki/Vishnu" title="Vishnu">Vishnu</a> who will usher in a new Golden Age (<a href="/wiki/Satya_Yuga" title="Satya Yuga">Satya Yuga</a>).</p>\n<p>Whatever its historical basis, Shambhala gradually came to be seen as a Buddhist <a href="/wiki/Pure_Land" class="mw-redirect" title="Pure Land">Pure Land</a>, a fabulous kingdom whose reality is visionary or spiritual as much as physical or geographic. It was in this form that the Shambhala myth reached the West, where it influenced non-Buddhist as well as Buddhist spiritual seekers \xe2\x80\x94 and, to some extent, popular culture in general.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Nominate/Selected_concept&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Nominate/Selected concept (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_concept&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Selected concept (page does not exist)">More concepts...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #B00760; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #B00760; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_biography/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_biography">Selected biography</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #B00760; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #E0C0D0;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="thumb tnone">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:152px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Kobo_Daishi.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Kobo_Daishi.jpg/150px-Kobo_Daishi.jpg" width="150" height="186" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Kobo_Daishi.jpg/225px-Kobo_Daishi.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Kobo_Daishi.jpg/300px-Kobo_Daishi.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2106" data-file-height="2605" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Kobo_Daishi.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nWooden statue of Kukai.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>K\xc5\xabkai</b> (<span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">\xe7\xa9\xba\xe6\xb5\xb7</span>) or also known posthumously as <b>K\xc5\x8db\xc5\x8d-Daishi</b> (<span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">\xe5\xbc\x98\xe6\xb3\x95\xe5\xa4\xa7\xe5\xb8\xab</span>), <a href="/wiki/774" title="774">774</a>\xe2\x80\x93<a href="/wiki/835" title="835">835</a> <a href="/wiki/Common_Era" title="Common Era">CE</a> was a <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japanese</a> <a href="/wiki/Bhikshu" class="mw-redirect" title="Bhikshu">monk</a>, <a href="/wiki/Scholar" class="mw-redirect" title="Scholar">scholar</a>, <a href="/wiki/Poet" title="Poet">poet</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Artist" title="Artist">artist</a>, founder of the <a href="/wiki/Shingon" class="mw-redirect" title="Shingon">Shingon</a> or "True Word" school of <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhism</a>.</p>\n<p>K\xc5\xabkai is famous as a <a href="/wiki/Calligraphy" title="Calligraphy">calligrapher</a> (see <i><a href="/wiki/Shodo" class="mw-redirect" title="Shodo">Shodo</a></i>), <a href="/wiki/Engineer" title="Engineer">engineer</a>, and is said to have invented <i><a href="/wiki/Kana" title="Kana">kana</a>,</i> the syllabary in which, in combination with Chinese characters (<i><a href="/wiki/Kanji" title="Kanji">Kanji</a></i>) the <a href="/wiki/Japanese_language" title="Japanese language">Japanese</a> language is written (although this claim has not been proven).</p>\n<p>His religious writing, some fifty works, expound the esoteric Shingon doctrine, of which the major ones have been translated into English by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Yoshito_Hakeda&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Yoshito Hakeda (page does not exist)">Yoshito Hakeda</a> (see references below). K\xc5\xabkai is also said to have written the <i><a href="/wiki/Iroha" title="Iroha">iroha</a>,</i> one of the most famous poems in <a href="/wiki/Japanese_language" title="Japanese language">Japanese</a>, which uses every phonetic <i>kana</i> syllable.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Nominate/Selected_biography&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Nominate/Selected biography (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Selected_biography&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Vajrayana Buddhism/Selected biography (page does not exist)">More biographies...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #B00760; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #B00760; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Vajrayana_Buddhism/Categories&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Categories">Categories</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #B00760; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #E0C0D0;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="CategoryTreeTag" data-ct-mode="0" data-ct-options="{&quot;mode&quot;:0,&quot;hideprefix&quot;:20,&quot;showcount&quot;:false,&quot;namespaces&quot;:false}">\n<div class="CategoryTreeSection">\n<div class="CategoryTreeItem"><span class="CategoryTreeBullet"><span class="CategoryTreeToggle" style="display: none;" data-ct-title="Vajrayana" title="collapse" data-ct-loaded="1" data-ct-state="expanded">\xe2\x96\xbc</span></span> <a class="CategoryTreeLabel  CategoryTreeLabelNs14 CategoryTreeLabelCategory" href="/wiki/Category:Vajrayana">Vajrayana</a></div>\n<div class="CategoryTreeChildren" style="display:block">\n<div class="CategoryTreeSection">\n<div class="CategoryTreeItem"><span class="CategoryTreeBullet"><span class="CategoryTreeToggle" style="display: none;" data-ct-title="Buddhist_tantras" title="expand" data-ct-state